---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', text: 'Quick Verdict', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Side-by-Side Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'safetywing', text: 'SafetyWing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'img', text: 'IMG Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'cigna', text: 'Cigna Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'founder-needs', text: 'Startup Founder Priorities', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Which Is Best For You?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { href: '/insurance-for/digital-nomads', text: 'Digital Nomad Insurance' },
  { href: '/insurance-for/remote-workers', text: 'Remote Worker Insurance' },
  { href: '/providers/safetywing', text: 'SafetyWing Review' },
  { href: '/providers/img-global', text: 'IMG Global Review' },
  { href: '/providers/cigna-global', text: 'Cigna Global Review' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
];

const mainComparisonRows = [
  { feature: 'Monthly Cost (35)', safetywing: '$45-56', img: '$150-300', cigna: '$350-500' },
  { feature: 'Coverage Limit', safetywing: '$250,000', img: '$1M-5M', cigna: 'Unlimited' },
  { feature: 'US Coverage', safetywing: 'Limited (30 days)', img: 'Optional', cigna: 'Optional' },
  { feature: 'Pre-existing Conditions', safetywing: 'Excluded', img: 'Limited', cigna: 'Can be covered' },
  { feature: 'Mental Health', safetywing: 'Crisis only', img: 'Limited', cigna: 'Comprehensive' },
  { feature: 'Telemedicine', safetywing: 'Included', img: 'Included', cigna: 'Included' },
  { feature: 'Flexibility', safetywing: 'Month-to-month', img: 'Annual', cigna: 'Annual' },
  { feature: 'Maternity', safetywing: 'Not covered', img: 'Optional rider', cigna: 'Comprehensive' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Solo founder (30)', safetywing: '$45/mo', img: '$150-220/mo', cigna: '$320-400/mo' },
  { profile: 'Solo founder (40)', safetywing: '$67/mo', img: '$220-350/mo', cigna: '$450-600/mo' },
  { profile: 'Founder + partner', safetywing: '$90/mo', img: '$320-500/mo', cigna: '$650-900/mo' },
  { profile: 'Family (2 founders + kid)', safetywing: '$145/mo', img: '$500-800/mo', cigna: '$950-1,300/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="SafetyWing vs IMG vs Cigna for Startup Founders | 2025 Comparison"
  description="Compare health insurance for startup founders: SafetyWing's budget option, IMG's mid-tier coverage, and Cigna's premium plans. Expert analysis for bootstrapped to funded startups."
  headline="SafetyWing vs IMG vs Cigna: Insurance for Startup Founders"
  subheadline="From bootstrapped to Series A—find the right health coverage for your founder journey, budget, and risk tolerance."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/get-quotes"
>
  <section id="quick-verdict" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Quick Verdict</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary-800 mb-2">SafetyWing</h3>
        <p class="text-primary-700 mb-3">Best for Bootstrapped</p>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-4">Ultra-affordable coverage when you're burning runway on product, not premiums. Month-to-month flexibility matches startup uncertainty.</p>
        <a href="/providers/safetywing" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded hover:bg-primary-700 transition text-sm" style="color: white !important;">Learn More</a>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border border-purple-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-purple-800 mb-2">IMG Global</h3>
        <p class="text-purple-700 mb-3">Best Mid-Stage</p>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-4">When you've raised a seed round and can afford real coverage. Solid protection without corporate pricing.</p>
        <a href="/providers/img-global" class="inline-block bg-purple-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded hover:bg-purple-700 transition text-sm" style="color: white !important;">Learn More</a>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">Cigna Global</h3>
        <p class="text-green-700 mb-3">Best Funded</p>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-4">Premium coverage when investor money allows proper protection. Comprehensive benefits you'd expect from a well-funded company.</p>
        <a href="/providers/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-green-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded hover:bg-green-700 transition text-sm" style="color: white !important;">Learn More</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="comparison-table" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </section>

  <section id="safetywing" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">SafetyWing</h2>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
      <span class="bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Bootstrapped Budget</span>
      <span class="bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Month-to-Month</span>
      <span class="bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Startup-Friendly</span>
    </div>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">SafetyWing was literally built by startup founders for startup founders. The Nomad Insurance product costs less than a typical SaaS subscription—about $45/month—making it accessible even when you're pre-revenue and watching every dollar of runway.</p>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">The month-to-month structure means no annual commitment. If your startup fails (or succeeds and you get corporate coverage), you can cancel anytime. Coverage is basic but covers emergencies, hospitalizations, and even some home country visits—essential when you're bouncing between co-working spaces globally.</p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">Founder Strengths</h4>
        <ul class="text-green-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• Lowest cost in market</li>
          <li>• Month-to-month flexibility</li>
          <li>• Sign up in minutes</li>
          <li>• Global coverage (190+ countries)</li>
          <li>• Telemedicine included</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-amber-800 mb-2">Limitations</h4>
        <ul class="text-amber-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• $250K limit may be insufficient</li>
          <li>• Pre-existing conditions excluded</li>
          <li>• Limited US coverage (30 days/90)</li>
          <li>• No maternity coverage</li>
          <li>• Basic mental health coverage</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <a href="/providers/safetywing" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get SafetyWing Quote</a>
  </section>

  <section id="img" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">IMG Global</h2>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
      <span class="bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Seed Stage</span>
      <span class="bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Solid Coverage</span>
      <span class="bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">US Options</span>
    </div>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">IMG Global hits the sweet spot for funded founders who need real coverage but aren't ready for corporate-level premiums. Their Global Medical Insurance offers $1M-5M in coverage—enough for serious medical events that could otherwise bankrupt a young company.</p>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">The US coverage option is valuable if you're building in the Bay Area or NYC while maintaining global mobility. IMG's plans can be customized—add outpatient, adjust deductibles, include wellness. You get real insurance without Fortune 500 pricing.</p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">Founder Strengths</h4>
        <ul class="text-green-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• $1M-5M coverage limits</li>
          <li>• US coverage available</li>
          <li>• Customizable plans</li>
          <li>• Good direct billing network</li>
          <li>• Maternity rider available</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-amber-800 mb-2">Considerations</h4>
        <ul class="text-amber-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• Annual commitment required</li>
          <li>• Pre-existing condition limitations</li>
          <li>• Mental health limits</li>
          <li>• US coverage adds significant cost</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <a href="/providers/img-global" class="inline-block bg-purple-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-purple-700 transition font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get IMG Quote</a>
  </section>

  <section id="cigna" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Cigna Global</h2>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
      <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Series A+</span>
      <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Premium Coverage</span>
      <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Scalable</span>
    </div>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">Cigna Global is what you graduate to when you've raised real money and can afford proper protection. Unlimited coverage means no worrying about caps during a serious illness. Comprehensive mental health coverage matters when founder stress is real and burnout rates are high.</p>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">This is also the strategic choice if you're planning to hire international employees—Cigna offers group plans that scale. Pre-existing conditions can often be covered after waiting periods, valuable if you've delayed insurance while bootstrapping and now have documented health issues.</p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">Founder Strengths</h4>
        <ul class="text-green-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• Unlimited coverage</li>
          <li>• Comprehensive mental health</li>
          <li>• Pre-existing conditions coverage</li>
          <li>• Scales to team plans</li>
          <li>• Maternity coverage included</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-amber-800 mb-2">Considerations</h4>
        <ul class="text-amber-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• Highest premiums</li>
          <li>• Annual commitment</li>
          <li>• Overkill for early-stage</li>
          <li>• Complex plan options</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <a href="/providers/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-green-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-green-700 transition font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
  </section>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Quotes for Your Stage"
    description="Get personalized quotes based on your startup stage and coverage needs."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
  />

  <section id="pricing" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Pricing Comparison</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">Insurance cost as a percentage of runway matters—here's what to budget:</p>
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-4">*SafetyWing is month-to-month; IMG and Cigna are annual. US coverage adds 30-50% to IMG/Cigna pricing.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="founder-needs" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Startup Founder Priorities</h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Budget Reality</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-4">At different stages, insurance budget varies dramatically:</p>
        <ul class="text-neutral-700 text-sm space-y-2">
          <li>• <strong>Pre-seed:</strong> $50-100/mo is realistic</li>
          <li>• <strong>Seed ($500K-2M):</strong> $150-300/mo reasonable</li>
          <li>• <strong>Series A+:</strong> $400-600/mo appropriate</li>
          <li>• Remember: founder health is a company asset</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Flexibility Needs</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-4">Startup life is unpredictable—insurance should match:</p>
        <ul class="text-neutral-700 text-sm space-y-2">
          <li>• Location changes (visa runs, pivots)</li>
          <li>• Income fluctuations</li>
          <li>• Company milestones triggering upgrades</li>
          <li>• Exit scenarios (acquisition, employment)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-800 mb-3">Common Founder Mistakes</h3>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-bold text-blue-800 mb-2">Don't Do This</h4>
          <ul class="text-blue-700 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>• Going completely uninsured to save money</li>
            <li>• Over-insuring and burning runway</li>
            <li>• Ignoring mental health coverage</li>
            <li>• Not reading exclusions carefully</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-bold text-blue-800 mb-2">Do This Instead</h4>
          <ul class="text-blue-700 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>• Start with basic coverage, upgrade with funding</li>
            <li>• Match coverage to actual risk exposure</li>
            <li>• Prioritize mental health as a founder</li>
            <li>• Review policy at each funding milestone</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="best-for" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Which Is Best For You?</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="bg-primary-50 border-l-4 border-primary-600 p-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-primary-800 mb-2">Choose SafetyWing if:</h3>
        <ul class="text-primary-700 space-y-1">
          <li>• You're bootstrapped or pre-seed</li>
          <li>• Budget is under $100/month</li>
          <li>• You're healthy with no pre-existing conditions</li>
          <li>• Flexibility matters more than comprehensive coverage</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-l-4 border-purple-600 p-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-purple-800 mb-2">Choose IMG Global if:</h3>
        <ul class="text-purple-700 space-y-1">
          <li>• You've raised seed funding</li>
          <li>• You need US coverage occasionally</li>
          <li>• $150-300/month is comfortable</li>
          <li>• You want customizable coverage options</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-600 p-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">Choose Cigna Global if:</h3>
        <ul class="text-green-700 space-y-1">
          <li>• You've raised Series A or beyond</li>
          <li>• Mental health coverage is important</li>
          <li>• You have or expect pre-existing conditions</li>
          <li>• You're planning to hire international team</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="faqs" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-2">Can my startup pay for my insurance?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">Yes, and it's often tax-advantaged. Many jurisdictions allow health insurance as a deductible business expense. Consult your accountant, but this can effectively reduce your cost by your tax rate. Even pre-revenue startups can set this up properly.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-2">What if I get acquired or shut down?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">SafetyWing's month-to-month structure is ideal for uncertainty—just cancel when you get corporate coverage. Annual plans with IMG or Cigna may have cancellation policies; check terms. If acquired, negotiate to maintain coverage during transition periods.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-2">How do I handle insurance for co-founders?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">Each co-founder typically gets individual policies at early stage. After raising, consider group plans—Cigna and IMG offer small group options starting at 2-3 people. This often provides better rates and easier administration than individual policies.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-2">Should I include insurance in my fundraising budget?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">Absolutely. Smart founders include $5-10K annually for founder health insurance in their budget. Investors understand that a sick founder is a company risk. Many accelerators (like Y Combinator) even mandate health insurance.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="bg-neutral-100 rounded-lg p-6 text-sm text-neutral-600">
    <p><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Insurance pricing and coverage details change frequently. Startup circumstances vary widely—this guide provides general direction, not specific advice. Always verify coverage directly with providers before purchasing. This comparison is for informational purposes only.</p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
